Revert the following patch for the LTS OmniOS release:

Subject: [PATCH] curl: ignore options asking for SSLv2 or SSLv3
Instead output a warning about it and continue with the defaults.

diff -wpruN '--exclude=*.orig' a~/docs/cmdline-opts/sslv2.d a/docs/cmdline-opts/sslv2.d
--- a~/docs/cmdline-opts/sslv2.d	1970-01-01 00:00:00
+++ a/docs/cmdline-opts/sslv2.d	1970-01-01 00:00:00
@@ -9,5 +9,6 @@ See-also: http1.1 http2
 Help: Use SSLv2
 Category: tls
 ---
-This option previously asked curl to use SSLv2, but starting in curl 7.77.0 this
-instruction is ignored. SSLv2 is widely considered insecure (see RFC 6176).
+Forces curl to use SSL version 2 when negotiating with a remote SSL
+server. Sometimes curl is built without SSLv2 support. SSLv2 is widely
+considered insecure (see RFC 6176).
diff -wpruN '--exclude=*.orig' a~/docs/cmdline-opts/sslv3.d a/docs/cmdline-opts/sslv3.d
--- a~/docs/cmdline-opts/sslv3.d	1970-01-01 00:00:00
+++ a/docs/cmdline-opts/sslv3.d	1970-01-01 00:00:00
@@ -9,6 +9,6 @@ See-also: http1.1 http2
 Help: Use SSLv3
 Category: tls
 ---
-This option previously asked curl to use SSLv3, but starting in curl 7.77.0
-this instruction is ignored. SSLv3 is widely considered insecure (see RFC
-7568).
+Forces curl to use SSL version 3 when negotiating with a remote SSL
+server. Sometimes curl is built without SSLv3 support. SSLv3 is widely
+considered insecure (see RFC 7568).
diff -wpruN '--exclude=*.orig' a~/src/tool_getparam.c a/src/tool_getparam.c
--- a~/src/tool_getparam.c	1970-01-01 00:00:00
+++ a/src/tool_getparam.c	1970-01-01 00:00:00
@@ -1307,11 +1307,11 @@ ParameterError getparameter(const char *
       break;
     case '2':
       /* SSL version 2 */
-      warnf(global, "Ignores instruction to use SSLv2\n");
+      config->ssl_version = CURL_SSLVERSION_SSLv2;
       break;
     case '3':
       /* SSL version 3 */
-      warnf(global, "Ignores instruction to use SSLv3\n");
+      config->ssl_version = CURL_SSLVERSION_SSLv3;
       break;
     case '4':
       /* IPv4 */
